                            <comment id="13976358" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 22 Apr 2014 04:21:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you review &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=dbrosius&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;dbrosius&quot;&gt;dbrosius&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13976402" author="dbrosius" created="Tue, 22 Apr 2014 05:18:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;patch(es) LGTM +1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;as a side note, and unrelated to this patch, nodetool rebuild_index silently ignores bad index names, so it appears that a rebuild of a fictional index succeeded.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;ie&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;./nodetool rebuild_index ks cf foobar;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;seems to complete successfully after churning for a short time.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;probably not ideal.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
